post_text:
Attention Parents of 4K-5 students:

Grades 4K-5 are defined as the critical foundational years for students, especially grades 4K-3. During this time, students are learning letter sounds, reading skills, number sense, and mathematical strategies. Currently there is not a comprehensive standards based online program that addresses the unique needs of elementary students in isolation of a teacher. Districts who are able to provide a virtual option for grades 4K- 5 utilize a classroom teacher to provide live instruction and support. At this time we are not able to expand our staffing to include elementary teachers to provide complete virtual education.

post_text:
To ensure that we are adequately prepared for re-opening in the fall and the increase in COVID cases, Florence Four has revised the 2020-21 Academic Calendar to included a later start date. Based on the new calendar students will return on August 17.

In addition, registration for the upcoming year will be completed online. Registration letters with the parent login information has been mailed. Please visit our website to complete the online registration form for the fall.

Lastly, Florence Four reopening options for the fall will be released on July 16. A parent survey will be distributed with the reopening options to solicit your feedback and choice.

To ensure that we are adequately prepared for re-opening in the fall and the increase in COVID cases, Florence Four has revised the 2020-21 Academic Calendar to included a later start date. Based on the new calendar students will return on August 17.

In addition, registration for the upcoming year will be completed online. Registration letters with the parent login information has been mailed. Please visit our website to complete the online registration form for the fall.

Lastly, Florence Four reopening options for the fall will be released on July 16. A parent survey will be distributed with the reopening options to solicit your feedback and choice.

This is a reminder that teacher office hours are Monday-Friday from 9 to 11 am and from 1 to 3 pm through google classroom and class dojo. Please feel free to contact teachers if you need assistance. E-Learning days counts towards attendance. Please make sure your students are completing their assignments.

Additionally, please visit our website for updated information as well as meal delivery times and locations.

If you have any questions, please contact the principals at (843) 346-3956 extension 2101 for elementary parents and 4101 for middle and high school questions.

post_text:
Due to inclement weather, all Florence County School District Four Schools, will be dismissed at 1 pm today, February 6, 2020. In addition, all after school programs and activities have been canceled.

We apologize for any inconvenience this may have caused; however, the safety of our students, parents, faculty, and staff is of importance. Please be safe.
text:
Due to inclement weather, all Florence County School District Four Schools, will be dismissed at 1 pm today, February 6, 2020. In addition, all after school programs and activities have been canceled.

We apologize for any inconvenience this may have caused; however, the safety of our students, parents, faculty, and staff is of importance. Please be safe.

post_text: Today our JROTC department put on a Veterans Day Breakfast event to commemorate our Veterans, Service Members, and their families. Over 75 personnel came out in support of this event. The program highlighted our guest speaker, CPT Zahra Moutabakkir for Fort Jackson, SC and our very own Timmonsville Concert Band. The program was led by our JROTC chain of command, c/LTC Yobana Rojas-Moreno, c/CSM Trinity Echols and c/MAJ Courtney Ashley. Great Job and GO WHIRLWINDS! #Florence4Strong #DareToBelieve

post_text:
💥Florence 4 Scholar Alert 💥💥💥💥💥💥💥💥💥
Students from Timmonsville Band auditioned for band scholarships at Allen University, Benedict College and Johnson C. Smith University. Allen University expressed interest in Herbert Bines and plans to make him a scholarship offer. He was also offered $2,000 from Benedict College for academics. Latavia Harris was offered $10,000 from Johnson C. Smith University. She will receive an additional $1000 for being a music major. Maleyah Burroughs also received $10,000 from Johnson C Smith and $12,000 from Benedict College. She also received $5000 from Benedict in an academic scholarship. In total, the students were awarded $39,000 in scholarship offers with $32,000 for band in one day. #Florence4Strong #DareToBelieve
